Note: ─── Start Bot ───────────────────────────────────────
Say "═══════════════════════════════════════════"
Say "  EPL Discord Bot v" + VERSION
Say "  Commands: !help, !hello, !about, !syntax, !example, !quote, !stats"
Say "  DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN = env var to connect"
Say "═══════════════════════════════════════════"

Note: In a full implementation, this would use the discord.py event loop:
Note:   client = discord.Client()
Note:   @client.event
Note:   async def on_message(message):
Note:       response = handle_message(message.content)
Note:       if response: await message.channel.send(response)
Note:   client.run(TOKEN)

Say "Bot handler ready. Connect to Discord with your token to go live."
